<h3>Formattazione della DATA e ORA</h3>
<p>Il valore data e ora del campo "created_at" del primo utente <code>current_user.created_at</code>: <strong><%= current_user.created_at %></strong></p>
<p>stesso valore formattato <code>current_user.created_at.strftime("%A %d %^B %Y at %H:%M and %S seconds")</code>: <strong><%= current_user.created_at.strftime("%A %d %^B %Y at %H:%M and %S seconds") %></strong></p>

<hr/>

<p>Esprimiamo un valore data e ora come stringa <code>"2022-10-08 23:30:28 UTC"</code>: <strong><%= "2022-10-08 23:30:28 UTC" %></strong></p>
<p>Se proviamo ad applicare la formattazione <code>"2022-10-08 23:30:28 UTC".strftime("day %d %^B %Y")</code> abbiamo un errore: <strong><code>ERROR: undefined method `strftime' for "2022-10-08 23:30:28 UTC":String</code></strong></p>

<hr/>

<p>Convertiamo la stringa ad un tipo data, ma senza l'orario <code>"2022-10-08 23:30:28 UTC".to_date</code>: <strong><%= "2022-10-08 23:30:28 UTC".to_date %></strong></p>
<p>Se formattiamo l'orario è tutto a zero <code>"2022-10-08 23:30:28 UTC".to_date.strftime("%A %d %^B %Y at %H:%M and %S seconds")</code>: <strong><%= "2022-10-08 23:30:28 UTC".to_date.strftime("%A %d %^B %Y at %H:%M and %S seconds") %></strong></p>

<hr/>

<p>Convertiamo la stringa ad un tipo data con l'orario <code>"2022-10-08 23:30:28 UTC".to_datetime</code>: <strong><%= "2022-10-08 23:30:28 UTC".to_datetime %></strong></p>
<p>Se formattiamo abbiamo anche l'orario <code>"2022-10-08 23:30:28 UTC".to_datetime.strftime("%A %d %^B %Y at %H:%M and %S seconds")</code>: <strong><%= "2022-10-08 23:30:28 UTC".to_datetime.strftime("%A %d %^B %Y at %H:%M and %S seconds") %></strong></p>

<hr/><br/>

<h4> Qualche esempio con .strftime() usato direttamente. --> non ho la traduzione nelle varie lingue(i18n) </h4>
<p><code>"2022-10-08 23:30:28 UTC".to_datetime.strftime("%A %d %^B %Y at %H:%M and %S seconds")</code>: <strong><%= "2022-10-08 23:30:28 UTC".to_datetime.strftime("%A %d %^B %Y at %H:%M and %S seconds") %></strong></p>
<p><code>"2022-10-08 23:30:28 UTC".to_datetime.strftime("Today is %d %^B %Y")</code>: <strong><%= "2022-10-08 23:30:28 UTC".to_datetime.strftime("Today is %d %^B %Y") %></strong></p>

<hr/><br/>

<h4> Qualche esempio tramite i files in <code>config/locales/</code> --> ho la traduzione nelle varie lingue (i18n) </h4>
<p><q>Usano la stessa sintassi di .strftime() </q></p>
<p><code>l "2022-10-08 23:30:28 UTC".to_date, format: :long</code>: <strong><%= l "2022-10-08 23:30:28 UTC".to_date, format: :long %></strong></p>
<p><code>l "2022-10-08 23:30:28 UTC".to_datetime, format: :long</code>: <strong><%= l "2022-10-08 23:30:28 UTC".to_datetime, format: :long %></strong></p>
<p><code>l "2022-10-08 23:30:28 UTC".to_date, format: :short</code>: <strong><%= l "2022-10-08 23:30:28 UTC".to_date, format: :short %></strong></p>
<p><code>l "2022-10-08 23:30:28 UTC".to_datetime, format: :short</code>: <strong><%= l "2022-10-08 23:30:28 UTC".to_datetime, format: :short %></strong></p>
<p><code>l "2022-10-08 23:30:28 UTC".to_datetime, format: :my_custom_long</code>: <strong><%= l "2022-10-08 23:30:28 UTC".to_datetime, format: :my_custom_long %></strong></p>

